 For thou hast been a helper to every lowly city, and a shelter to them that were disheartened by reason of poverty: thou shalt deliver them from wicked men: [thou hast been] a shelter of them that thirst, and a refreshing air to injured men. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 5.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  We [were] as faint-hearted men thirsting in Sion, by reason of ungodly men to whom thou didst deliver us. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 6.}{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  And the Lord of hosts shall make [a feast] for all the nations: on this mount they shall drink gladness, they shall drink wine: }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 7.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 they shall anoint themselves with ointment in this mountain. Impart thou all these things to the nations; for this is [God's] counsel upon all the nations. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 8.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 Death has prevailed and swallowed [men] up; but again the Lord God has taken away every tear from every face. He has taken away the reproach of [his] people from all the earth: for the mouth off the Lord has spoken it. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 9.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  And in that day they shall say,
 behold our God in whom we have trusted, and he shall save us: this [is] the Lord; we have waited for him, and we have exulted, and will rejoice in our salvation. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 
\par }\pard \s21\qj \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 
