 The mouth of an understanding man is praised by a man; but he that is dull of heart is had in derision. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 9.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 Better is a man in dishonor serving himself, than one honoring himself and wanting bread. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 10.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  A righteous man has pity for the lives of his cattle; 
but the bowels of the ungodly are unmerciful. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 11.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 He that tills his own land shall be satisfied with bread; but they that pursue vanities are void of understanding. He that enjoys himself in banquets of wine, shall leave dishonor in his own strong holds. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 12.}{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  The desires of the ungodly are evil; but the roots of the godly are firmly set. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 13.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 For the sin of his lips a sinner falls into snares; but a righteous man escapes from them. He whose looks are gentle shall be pitied, but he that contends in the gates will afflict souls. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 14.}{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  The soul of a man shall be filled with good from the fruits of his mouth; and the recompense of his lips shall be given to him. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 15.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 The ways of fools are right in their own eyes; but a wise man hearkens to counsels. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 16.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  A fool declares his wrath the same day; but a prudent man hides his own disgrace. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 17.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  A righteous man declares the open truth; but an unjust witness is deceitful. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 18.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 Some wound as they speak, like swords; but the tongues of the wise heal. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 19.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  True lips establish testimony; but a hasty witness has an unjust tongue. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 20.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  There is deceit in the heart of him that imagines evil; but they that love peace shall rejoice. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 21.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 No injustice will please a just man; but the ungodly will be filled with mischief. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 22.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  Lying lips are an
 abomination to the Lord; but he that deals faithfully is accepted with him. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 
