 And Sem and Japheth having taken a garment, put it on both their backs and went backwards, and covered the nakedness of their father; and their face was backward and they saw not the nakedness of their father. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 
24.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  And Noe recovered from the wine, and knew all that his younger son had done to him. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 25.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  And he said, Cursed b
e the servant Chanaan, a slave shall he be to his brethren. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 26.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  And he said, Blessed be the Lord God of Sem, and Chanaan shall be his bond-servant. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 27.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  May God make room for Japheth, and let him dwell in the habitations of Sem, and let Chanaan be his servant. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 28.}{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  And Noe lived after the flood three hundred and fifty years. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 29.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  And all the days of Noe were nine hundred and fifty years, and he died. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 1.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  Now these are the generations of the sons of Noe, Sem, Cham, Japheth; and sons were born to them after the flood. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 
