 game; but a blameless man is a precious possession. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 28.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  In the ways of righteousness is life; but the ways of those that remember injuries lead to death. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 1.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  A wise son is obedient to his father: but a disobedient son will be destroyed. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 2.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  A good man shall
 eat of the fruits of righteousness: but the lives of transgressors shall perish before their time. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 3.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 He that keeps his own mouth keeps his own life: but he that is hasty with his lips shall bring terror upon himself. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 4.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  Every slothful man desires, but th
e hands of the active are diligent. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 5.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  A righteous man hates an unjust word: but an ungodly man is ashamed, and will have no confidence. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 7.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  There are some who, having nothing, enrich themselves: and there are some who bring themselves down in the midst of much wealth. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 8.}{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  A man's own wealth is the ransom of his life: but the poor endures not threatening. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 9.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 The righteous always have light: but the light of the ungodly is quenched. Crafty souls go astray in sins: but just men pity, and are merciful. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 
