he word of the Lord, ye afflicted men, and ye princes of this people that is in Jerusalem. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 15.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 ye have said, We have made a covenant with Hades, and agreements with death; if the rushing storm should pass, it shall not come upon us: we have made falsehood our hope, and by falsehood shall we be protected: }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 
16.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  Therefore thus saith the Lord, [even] the Lord. Behold, I lay for the foundations of Sion a costly stone, a choice, a corner-stone, a precious [stone], for its foundations; and he that believes [on him]
 shall by no means be ashamed. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 17.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 And I will cause judgment [to be] for hope, and my compassion shall be for [just] measures, and ye that trust vainly in falsehood [shall fall]: for the storm shall by no means pass by you, }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 18.}{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  except it also take away your covenant of death, and your trust in Hades shall by no means stand: if the rushing storm should come upon you, ye shall be beaten down by it. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 19.}{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  Whenever it shall pass by, it shall take you; morning by morning it shall pass by in the day, and in the night there shall be an evil hope.  Learn to hear, }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 20.}{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  ye that are distressed; we cannot fight, but we are ourselves too weak for you to be gathered. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 21.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 Lord shall rise up as a mountain of ungodly [men], and shall be in the valley of Gabaon; he shall perform his works with wrath, [even] a work of bitterness, and his wrath shall deal strangely, and his destruction shall be strange. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 22.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  Therefore do not ye rejoice, neither let your bands be made strong; for I have heard of works finished and cut short by the
 Lord of hosts, which he will execute upon all the earth. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 
