 And the Lord said to Abram, Go forth out of thy land and out of thy kindred, and out of the house of thy father, and come into the land which shall show thee. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 2.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 And I will make thee a great nation, and I will bless thee and magnify thy name, and thou shalt be blessed. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 3.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 And I will bless those that bless thee, and curse those that curse thee, and in thee shall all the tribes of the earth be blessed. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 4.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 And Abram went as the Lord spoke to him, and Lot departed with him, and Abram was seventy five years old, when he went out of Charrhan. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 5.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378 
 And Abram took Sara his wife, and Lot the son of his brother, and all their possessions, as many as they had got, and every soul which they had got in Charrhan, and they went forth to go into the land of Chanaan. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 6.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  And Abram traversed the land lengthwise as far as the place Sychem, to the high oak, and the Chananites then inhabited the land. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 7.}{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15671378  And the Lord appeared to Abram, and said to him, I will give this land to thy seed. And Abram built an altar there to the Lord who appeared to him. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid15671378\charrsid8870694 
